-JavaScript can run only one piece of work at a time.
-Blocking happens when JavaScript is busy for a long time, so it cannot move to the next line of code.
-Blocking happens when JavaScript is busy for a long time, so it cannot move to the next line of code.
-JavaScript gives any waiting tasks to the helper and continues useful work.
-A task is one full piece of work that JavaScript runs from start to end.





